In a bowl, combine candy and water. Cover and soak overnight; drain well and set aside. In a mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Beat in vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture. Fold in walnuts and candy. Spread into a greased 15-in. x 10-in. x 1-in. baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on a wire rack. Dust with confectioners' sugar. Cut into bars.